\begin_layout Standard
The goal of this section is to provide solutions to linear velocity and
 angular velocity for two bodies interacting in a perfectly elastic collision,
 where each body is free to rotate.
 The values necessary to solve this are: linear velocity, angular velocity,
 center of gravity, mass and inertial tensor for each body.
 Additionally, the point of collision and the normal vector for the collision,
 common to both bodies, must be known.
 The post-collision values to be solved for are linear velocity and angular
 velocity for each body.
